Business Brief -- Schwartz Brothers Inc.:
   Firm Exchanges 48% Stake
   For $20 Million in Loans
In the third quarter, the company's loss narrowed to
$128,000, or seven cents a share, from $3.1 million or $1.72
a share, a year earlier. Net sales declined 15% to $22.8
million. In the first nine months, the loss narrowed to $2.5
million, or $1.42 a share, from $2.9 million, or $1.62 a
share, a year earlier. Sales declined 27% to $60.5 million.